      About this item

      • A VERSATILE AIR FRYER AND MULTI-COOKER COMBO: Elevates practically any meal, from air frying quick after-school snacks to roasting for large gatherings.
      • PERFECTLY DONE TOAST: Oven turns off automatically when the toast countown timer ends - no burnt toast! Indicator light is red while toasting, blue when timer ends and oven turns off. Place rack at indicated toast position for ideal results.
      • 25 COOKING PRE-SETS: Provide a variety of cooking methods: Ribs, Defrost, Bake, Toast, Chicken, Pizza, Pastry, Slow Cook, Roast, Reheat, and Keep Warm.
      • DUAL-SPEED FAN: Golden fried crisping at it's finest with 360 superheated air circulation for your homemade cooking.
      • 26-QUART CAPACITY: This Extra-large 26-quart capacity countertop toaster is suitable for preparing food for 46 people with capacity to rotisserie a 6-lb chicken, bake a 12 pizza.
      • STAINLESS STEEL EXTERIOR: A stainless steel exterior provides a beautiful asthetic to any kitchen, taking your party hosting to the next level. And Elegant French doors open with a single pull interior light allows you to monitor food.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5 out of 5 stars
      So far, I love it! (Its definitely love)
      Update: Ive been using this oven for a couple months now for roasting, baking, broiling, air frying, and reheating. It is an outstanding oven that performs flawlessly every time. The oven heats evenly, so baked goods cook uniformly. Over the holidays I baked cookies, and since then enchiladas, cornbread, casseroles, sheet pan meals, hot wings, salmon, quesadillas, broiled sandwiches, etc. I love the amount of cooking space available and it doesnt take up too much counter space. This is the best toaster oven Ive owned. Absolutely love it!We purchased this oven to replace our Ninja Foodie flip-up air fryer/toaster oven which weve had for just over a year. We are full-time RVers and seldom bother to light and use the gas oven in our RV, so its very important to me that I have a good countertop oven. With limited space, I love that it doubles as an air fryer, too. We have a separate toaster because Ive never been satisfied with the way a toaster oven toasts (sounds silly, but give me a pop-up toaster any day).I never liked our old oven because its not tall enough inside to cook in anything but a tray. It was also not heating properly and I was very disappointed with the results. It dont heat properly and was too small to bake a cake or roast a whole chicken.I spent a lot of time researching other combination air fryer/ovens until I came upon this oven. I will update later, but I was very impressed with the cooking performance of my first meal - a sheet pan meal with Parmesan-crusted chicken breasts and broccoli. I baked it for 14 minutes at 425, turning the broccoli half way through. The chicken was perfectly cooked - juicy inside with a golden brown, crusty topping. The broccoli had the right amount of char without being over or undercooked. I was amazed how much better it roasted than the old oven and I like the way the baking tray just slips into the slots on the side. This meal wasnt very messy, so there wasnt much splatter and there were no drips to clean.Today Im baking cookies and tomorrow Im air frying wings, so I will update after Ive used it a few more times. We buy meal kits from Green Chef, and many of the recipes require baking. Since there are just two of us, this will definitely do the trick.This is a very preliminary review, but the positives include: roomy interior cooking space, easy to bake with a 9 square pan, pie pan, or 12 cookie sheet. Evenly heats and the temperature was consistent with a thermometer. It didnt overheat the room and we keep a 4-6 space from walls. The interior light is bright. I like the double doors, but be sure there is enough space to fully open them so they dont close on your hand - especially if its hot! There are many simple settings and its easy to adjust the temperature and time. Im looking forward to experimenting more! The only negative so far is that it cant accommodate the 12 pizza pan that worked with the old oven. This isnt a problem because Ive found frozen pizza is best when cooked on the wire rack instead of in a pan. We use our outdoor pizza oven for homemade pizza anyway.We will definitely stay on top of cleaning it after each use, wiping off splatters & drips that can smoke up the kitchen. Its not likely we will use the rotisserie because Im sure it would be very messy, but its going to be great for baking, roasting & air frying.More later after Ive used this for a few months, but if youve been considering getting this while its on sale - go for it!

      • DuckieDeb
        5.0 out of 5 stars So far, I love it! (Its definitely love)
        Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
        Verified Purchase
        Update: Ive been using this oven for a couple months now for roasting, baking, broiling, air frying, and reheating. It is an outstanding oven that performs flawlessly every time. The oven heats evenly, so baked goods cook uniformly. Over the holidays I baked cookies, and since then enchiladas, cornbread, casseroles, sheet pan meals, hot wings, salmon, quesadillas, broiled sandwiches, etc. I love the amount of cooking space available and it doesnt take up too much counter space. This is the best toaster oven Ive owned. Absolutely love it!

        We purchased this oven to replace our Ninja Foodie flip-up air fryer/toaster oven which weve had for just over a year. We are full-time RVers and seldom bother to light and use the gas oven in our RV, so its very important to me that I have a good countertop oven. With limited space, I love that it doubles as an air fryer, too. We have a separate toaster because Ive never been satisfied with the way a toaster oven toasts (sounds silly, but give me a pop-up toaster any day).

        I never liked our old oven because its not tall enough inside to cook in anything but a tray. It was also not heating properly and I was very disappointed with the results. It dont heat properly and was too small to bake a cake or roast a whole chicken.

        I spent a lot of time researching other combination air fryer/ovens until I came upon this oven. I will update later, but I was very impressed with the cooking performance of my first meal - a sheet pan meal with Parmesan-crusted chicken breasts and broccoli. I baked it for 14 minutes at 425, turning the broccoli half way through. The chicken was perfectly cooked - juicy inside with a golden brown, crusty topping. The broccoli had the right amount of char without being over or undercooked. I was amazed how much better it roasted than the old oven and I like the way the baking tray just slips into the slots on the side. This meal wasnt very messy, so there wasnt much splatter and there were no drips to clean.

        Today Im baking cookies and tomorrow Im air frying wings, so I will update after Ive used it a few more times. We buy meal kits from Green Chef, and many of the recipes require baking. Since there are just two of us, this will definitely do the trick.

        This is a very preliminary review, but the positives include: roomy interior cooking space, easy to bake with a 9 square pan, pie pan, or 12 cookie sheet. Evenly heats and the temperature was consistent with a thermometer. It didnt overheat the room and we keep a 4-6 space from walls. The interior light is bright. I like the double doors, but be sure there is enough space to fully open them so they dont close on your hand - especially if its hot! There are many simple settings and its easy to adjust the temperature and time. Im looking forward to experimenting more! The only negative so far is that it cant accommodate the 12 pizza pan that worked with the old oven. This isnt a problem because Ive found frozen pizza is best when cooked on the wire rack instead of in a pan. We use our outdoor pizza oven for homemade pizza anyway.

        We will definitely stay on top of cleaning it after each use, wiping off splatters & drips that can smoke up the kitchen. Its not likely we will use the rotisserie because Im sure it would be very messy, but its going to be great for baking, roasting & air frying.

        More later after Ive used this for a few months, but if youve been considering getting this while its on sale - go for it!

I love the fact that I can cook a small pizza in it without heating up my large oven! I LOVE the convenience of cooking multiple items at the same time (for 2 people) in a fraction of the time as a conventional oven. It sits on my counter top, so I'm using it all the time now.

      • Mimoki
        5.0 out of 5 stars Top top top. A game changer for us.
        Reviewed in Canada on March 22, 2025
        Verified Purchase
        After years of trying different kitchen appliances, this Emeril Lagasse French Door Air Fryer has completely replaced my regular oven. The 26-quart capacity might seem intimidating at first, but it fits perfectly on my counter without taking up too much space - truly a case of small but mighty. I love how the heat distribution works so evenly; everything from steaks to meatloaf comes out cooked uniformly, which has been an issue with other air fryers I've tried before.

        The doors are cleverly designed to open together with just one hand, making it convenient when my other hand is full of food to cook. I've had other air fryers (like my old Ninja) that simply can't compare to the quality and functionality of this one. Yes, there is some smoke that escapes from the corners of the doors during cooking, but this is actually normal for air frying - it's part of how the food gets that perfect crispy texture. One thing I didn't figure out right away was how to preheat it properly, as the instructions weren't very clear on this point. For anyone wondering, you need to use grill, roast or bake modes to get the "PH" symbol on the display, run it for a few minutes, then switch to your desired cooking mode.

        The 25 cooking functions give so much flexibility, and I've found the timer alarm system really helpful - it beeps halfway through cooking to remind you to flip food if needed, then beeps again when finished. The machine actually continues running for 1-2 minutes after cooking time ends to vent out hot air, which keeps your kitchen from overheating when you open the doors. As for cleaning, most parts are straightforward, though I recommend cleaning the drip pan after each use to avoid baked-on grease becoming difficult to remove. The heating elements do require special care - just soap and water, nothing abrasive.

        Overall, this air fryer does everything I need and more, reducing my need for cooking oils while still producing delicious food. It's become my go-to for nearly everything I cook, from simple vegetables to full meals, and the included accessories cover all basic needs.
